Came here with some friends before zoo lights. It was a great time! Really cool atmosphere and it is a big place! Huge menu and great food! The VIG Burger was delicious! I saw the VIG burger won the 2019 Chicago Burger Battle on Instagram so I had to try it! I had my burger with bacon and an egg. It was delicious! The fries and wings were good too! My wife had the chicken parmesan which she loved. People around us had the spreads which looked amazing! Next time I am getting that as an appetizer! Highly recommend! You will like this place!

Service and atmosphere are awesome. We had a party of six. Sat at high table in the back bar. Had the blister peppers pretzels and meatballs for appetizers. Meanwhile were so good three people ordered the meatball sandwich for dinner. Custom made  cocktails were delicious. I had the Vig Manhatten. Perfect. Make a reservation. This place is popular for good reason.

Also the sound system went out and no one in the venue seemed to care to make an annoucement that they were trying to fix it. The DJ was unconcerned. It was almost a good thing because the music was not great.

Got the chicken bun: good fluffy bun, but phenomenal fried chicken! Shishito peppers were amazing! Grilled without over burnt, not that gross bitter flavir, and only one was still uber spicy. Perfect!

The restaurant had a frenetic energy. It was packed but we were seated right away. My eye fell immediately on the lobster and waffles for brunch.  The lobster was delicious and it came with a pile of fresh greens. The waffle was doughy and tasted packaged. I love waffles so they need to be right...crispy on the outside and light and airy on the inside. Unfortunately that was not my experience.  The staff was super cool about it and only charged our table for one but we ordered two. I would have paid for the meal because  i don't expect that will love everything on the plate when trying a new place, but it was appreciated. Overall good experience and would definitely go back and take others. Enjoy!

The drink menu was good and had a plethora of options (no cognac though) and the ambiance is very professional and. comfortable. They also have a small area for those who wish to dine outside. Happy I came. If you are in the area, try it out.

To complicate matters, I'm a diabetic, so I can sometimes find it difficult to find good things for me to eat.  I ordered the meatballs, creamy califlour, and daily veg (spagetti squash).  The food was amazing and more than I can usually find or expect.  Plus my 7 year old destroyed two chicken baos and half of my wife's pretzel croissant with ham and cheese.  The food is worth every penny and I couldn't have been happier with the service.

Came here around midnight on a Saturday to join some friends for drinks. The queue to get inside wasn't that long. It was very packed though. Service was okay; we got our drinks fairly quickly.  The music playing was terrible. This is a biased opinion as I'm not a fan of pop music that's not Hip Hop or Reggaeton. The other patrons seemed to be enjoying themselves, then again they were pretty wasted. They should hire an actual DJ and not someone who comes in to set up a playlist on their laptop and leaves.  My music preferences being what they are, I can still tell if a DJ is good or not depending on how they play music and engage the crowd. In the one hour I was there, I heard songs getting repeated, at some point they started syning the music with the music video on the screens for no good reason. This playlist playing thing's name is Squeeze (it says DJ Squeeze on the screens but this thing doesn't deserve the designation of DJ. It's like calling a first semester pre-med dropout a doctor.) I'm pretty sure Squeeze is a rudimentary computer software they bought a few years back because it was playing hits between 2010 and 2015. The experience here would be a whole lot better if they just hire an actual human DJ that you can see working.  If you're not as sensitive to the music you're listening to as I am, you should visit, it's a decent place. If you are sensitive, stay away! I don't think I'm ever coming here again. I've learned my lesson, and I'll be staying away from white bars moving forward.
Loved it .. nice menu, good waiting staff .  Nice atmosphere .. we'll be back!

On vacation to Chicago and went for brunch today and was impressed with The Vig overall. Ordered the runny egg sandwich, chicken and waffles as well as the spicy pasta. Food was 100% on point. Food came out super fast, drinks were were on point (I had the Irish Iced Coffee) and our server was excellent as well. The decor is really cool, there’s some old scoreboard on the wall that was from 1949. The manager, Joe, was kind enough to explain the meaning of the “Vig” as well as give us a brief history lesson about sports betting. One thing I learned today was the Lakers originally came from Minnesota....makes complete sense now. I would recommend this place to anyone who wants solid food, great atmosphere and excellent service.
The Moroccan turkey burger was really unique and good
The atmosphere, service, and food excellent! I had the turkey burger and season fries, both were well seasoned and very tasty!

Food great, service superb. Not baby friendly. If no baby- 5 stars. If baby-2. I had the chorizo skillet for food which was incredible. The staff were also all very warm and welcoming, and will definitely be back the next time I’m in Chicago!

We had been hearing so much about “The Vig Burger” that we had to come try it after Lent. It did not disappoint! Wow... we also had a big appetite. We got fries, chicken parm sandwich, and the lobster roll. Honestly, the lobster roll wasn’t that phenomenal. The fries and dipping sauces were great tho!

An absolutely amazing meal. Lobster Deviled Eggs, Summer Berry Salad and pan seared Salmon With Thai Butter Sauce. This was so good it was like eating the brownie ends when I was a kid. Nice and crisp on the edges and phenomenal on the inside. Brooke was fantastic, attentive and well-versed in our delicious meal. During our wonderful eating experience we had 2 great drinks. The Making The Turn and a Bramblin Gramblin Man. These were followed up with a Wake Up Buttercup dessert cocktail. They were a taste bud explosion. It's my understanding they're opening up new locations, The Whale and Welcome Back in Logan Square sometime in July. This is absolutely a restaurant you don't want to miss. I only review The Best of the Best. Don't think about it, just go eat there. My advice, take it, it'll be the best decision you've made in a long time. Like and share. Follow me, I'll keep you well fed.

Very bad experience here. We were a bigger group of people and we took a chair from a table, instead of accommodating us the manager just told us to give the chair back when there were other tables with chairs that weren't used. Very rude!  Update: Hi Ryan, I'm glad that you actually read the reviews. Now here is my response to what you wrote. We weren't asking for the whole back area for ourselves, all we asked is a chair so we don't have to stand! If that's an unreasonable request then excuse my rudeness. On the other side, this is the action of a manager, not an employee. I would totally understand if one employee would have refused us one chair, but the manager? Now that's where I see that problem. If you want your business to be ran by those kind of people then that's your loss.  Bonus: This is not the first bad review you get regarding your manager or someone in charge there... Do you see my drift? Try to work on that. Cheers

We ordered the corn fritters (actually very good) and the fried chicken. The chicken was soggy, not crispy, and we weren’t told it would be steaks and not a half chicken. Also they would not allow substitutions in sides so we ordered a side of potatoes, which were bland. The Mac and cheese had good flavor but was cold when it came out. For 2 entrees and an appetizer, our bill came to $70 with tip, which seemed high for not great food.

If nothing would have gone wrong, I think I would have rated the Vig Chicago at 5 stars.  The wait staff was responsive and the food was generally good.  However, something did go wrong and the staff does not know how to deal with anything that does not run properly.  One of our entrées came out with a 12-inch long blue string from a kitchen towel embedded in the sandwich.  Not simply on the plate, but embedded in the sandwich.  This was pure negligence by the kitchen staff.  The management did offer to replace the meal and they did so.  However, any respectable restaurant would also comp the meal and often more.  They did not offer to comp the entrée.  I requested a comp for that entrée but they never verbally agreed.  When we received the receipt, the entrée was marked as comp AND they added a duplicate entrée at full price so that they would not lose any money.  The true test of service is when something goes wrong.  This was terrible customer service.  Revision 5/20/2018  The owner of the Vig Chicago reached out to me very soon after my review was posted and he invited us back for a better experience.  He apologized profusely for the negative experience and shared some information regarding what went wrong and the actions that he took to address the causes of the errors.  When we returned to take advantage of his invitation to give them another try, he met us at the door and again apologized and described what they did wrong and what they did to prevent similar errors in the future.  As I said in my initial review, the food and service were once again excellent.  And, of course, nothing went wrong!  However, that alone would not cause me to reverse my rating.  The reason why I feel good about going back to 5 stars is that the owner did not make excuses but rather, he owned what went wrong and was open about the actions that he took to correct them.  We will eat there again!

We arrived around 8ish, which I thought was perfect considering this is a pretty popular hang out spot and it gets quite packed as it gets later in the night, but I was wrong. We put in our names to get seated to a FOUR person table and they let us know it would be 20 mins so we went to order drinks at the bar towards the back of the restaurant (which again was a mission) and we never got sat at a table.
